org.hypknowsys.wumprep4weka.core.converters
Class WeblogLoader

java.lang.Object
  weka.core.converters.AbstractLoader
      org.hypknowsys.wumprep4weka.core.converters.WeblogLoader
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, weka.core.converters.BatchConverter, weka.core.converters.Loader, weka.core.OptionHandler, weka.gui.beans.Visible
public class WeblogLoader
extends weka.core.converters.AbstractLoader
implements weka.core.converters.BatchConverter, weka.core.OptionHandler, weka.gui.beans.Visible

Reads a Web server log file. The log file format must be specified in a WUMprep log file template, which in turn is specified in the WUMprep configuration file passed to this reader.

Available options are:
-C : The path of the configuration file to load.

Version:

setConfig

public void setConfig(WUMprepConfiguration config)
Sets the WUMprepConfiguration the loader should read its settings from. ATTENTION: The WUMprep Perl scripts allow to specify multiple log files at a time, which is reflected by the "inputLogs" setting in the config file being a multi-value setting. However, the current implementation of WUMprep4weka allows only to load a single log file (the main reason for this is that Weka doesn't support batch-processing in a similar way as WUMprep does). For this reason, ONLY THE FIRST LOGFILE DEFINED IN THE CONFIGURATION IS LOADED! Any other values are simply ignored by this loader.

Parameters:
config -
